 There are 4 major temples in the city. These are the temple of all- Father
 ODIN, which operate by royal appoinment; the temple of FREYA, a women only
 club; the temple of AEGIR, which goes in for a lot of meditation and incen-
 se and the temple of SET, an ancient snake god who  has blood stained alters
 and sacrifices concession. Temples operate much like Guilds. You stroll in,
 night or day, bump into the counter and they offer 3 options BUSINESS, 
 SERVICE or EXIT.

 If you select BUSINESS, they offer you membership of there order. Just like
 a Guild, there are fee's and challenges to be met. However, unlike joining
 a Guild, you don't just get your membership button and discount voucher, 
 you also get a spell book!

 Preist spells work just like magic spells(although the temples would never
 admit it), only you can access them through the PRIESTLY MAGIC icon. They
 are discribed on the following page.

 You can rise up through the ranks of a temple just like a Guild, by return-
 ing and selecting BUSINESS again. The higher you rise, the greater the magic
 you can cast. There are other perks too.

 The second option at a temple is SERVICE. Being responsible institutions,
 Temples Run free health checks for all citizens and tourists. The Healer will
 look you over, and recommend treatments for any ailments you may have, from
 dehydration (a visit to the tavern is cheaper) through combat injuries to 
 tomb rot, vampirism and watrs.

 The cure's arent cheap, but there effective! And members can operate an a
 "severe injury discount" basis, which keeps the cost very reasonable.

